OL,3,CPeanut allergy sufferers told to avoid
OL,4,Cmustard after contamination scare
OL,6,FPeople with a peanut allergy have been
OL,7,Fwarned to avoid eating products
OL,8,Fcontaining mustard because they may
OL,9,Fhave been contaminated.
OL,11,FMustard ingredients can be found in
OL,12,Ffood such as dips, sauces, salads and
OL,13,Fpre-packed sandwiches, the Food
OL,14,FStandards Agency (FSA) said.
OL,16,FSuch mustard products could contain
OL,17,Ftraces of peanut, potentially causing
OL,18,Fsevere reactions for those with an
OL,19,Fallergy.
