OL,3,CPeanut allergy sufferers told to avoid
OL,4,Cmustard after contamination scare
OL,6,FThe UK company affected, FGS
OL,7,FIngredients Ltd, has advised customers
OL,8,Fto remove from sale products
OL,9,Fcontaining the contaminated mustard
OL,10,Fingredients.
OL,12,FThere is no evidence other suppliers
OL,13,Fare affected so far, the agency added.
OL,15,FWhich products are being recalled
OL,16,Fbecause they may contain peanuts?
OL,18,F"If mustard is present in a food, it
OL,19,Fshould be labelled in bold on the
OL,20,Fpacket because it is an allergen
OL,21,Fitself," the FSA advised.
