OL,3,CPeanut allergy sufferers told to avoid
OL,4,Cmustard after contamination scare
OL,6,FFSA's director of food policy, Rebecca
OL,7,FSudworth, said: "Those with a peanut
OL,8,Fallergy should avoid consuming
OL,9,Fproducts containing mustard as an
OL,10,Fingredient until we identify the
OL,11,Findividual products affected.
OL,13,F"Parents and carers of children who
OL,14,Fhave a peanut allergy should take care
OL,15,Fto check the labels of food they buy
OL,16,Fand, if eating out, or getting a
OL,17,Ftakeaway, ask the restaurant or cafe
OL,18,Fabout foods that might contain mustard.
